p: The same measures were made at day 14 PI ( Table 2). For the 14 d PI bodies, the oral ID 50 for the TR and WT were Log 10 = 3.12 and Log 10 = 3.46, respectively. Two saliva samples were positive by CPE assay in the TR mosquito group at the highest dose (5.6 Log 10). All saliva samples were negative in WT mosquito groups. Overall, our infection and dissemination results showing limited vector competence were similar to those reported previously ( Brault et al. 2004) with this ONNV strain in A. gambiae, and there was no significant difference in infection rate between TR and WT groups at any dose.
